Bruce the baboon was released back into the wild. He's the primate that ran around Northcliff in Johannesburg last month. JOHANNESBURG - Bruce the baboon was released into the wild in Limpopo on Friday morning. Bruce made headlines while roaming the streets of Northcliff, Constantia Kloof and Krugersdorp last month. READ:Â 'Northcliff' baboon found He was finally captured by Community Led Animal Welfare (CLAW). He sustained superficial injuries trying to free himself from the trap but has since healed. 